  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail and chop the <strong>carrots</strong> and <strong>parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1581675056386-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1581675056386-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1581675056386-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1581675056386-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1581675056386-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top and tail the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, remove the skin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and cut into quarters</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> (skins on) by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Strip the <strong>rosemary </strong>and <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems, keeping them separate and discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1581675061510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1581675061510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1581675061510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1581675061510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1581675061510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong>, <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>carrots</strong>, <strong>parsnips</strong>,<strong> onion wedges</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or a large, deep baking tray)</p><p>Drizzle generously with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, add the <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Try to sit the green beans at the bottom of the tray so they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1581675066841-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1581675066841-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1581675066841-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1581675066841-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1581675066841-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Create a space in the middle of the tray and add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> (skin-side up)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Drizzle each chicken thigh with <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>thyme leaves </strong>over the chicken</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1581675072508-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1581675072508-x400.jpg",
